description:
&lt;h1&gt;Staff Nurse- Band 5&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting position available in this interesting, fast paced, but friendly outpatient department. We are a strong cohesive unit. We work independently with our clinical colleagues but also have a strong support network within our core team of nurses, HCA’s and Plaster technicians. We are part of a multidisciplinary team working here, in partnership with the Orthopaedic Surgeons, Advanced Orthopaedic Practitioners, the Trauma Team and Extended Scope Practitioners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we can offer you:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A fully supported induction programme, tailored to your needs, complete with a mentor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career progression within T and O covering nurse led dressing clinics, foot and ankle injection clinics, virtual fracture clinics and, given time, the opportunity to complete the Orthopaedic Practitioner course, which is a recognised qualification from the British Orthopaedic Association.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work with and support student nurses, our Trainee Nursing Associate who is working towards a Band 4, work experience students and the Band 2/3 apprenticeship training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We can offer you the opportunity to gain knowledge and skills working in the Trauma Assessment Unit alongside the Orthopaedic On call team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;IM(RE)R training leading to independently booking xrays for your clinic patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will gain knowledge and skills relating to Orthopaedic conditions and fractures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our department is open from 08.00hrs to 18:00hrs each weekday. We meet and treat a complete age range and diversity of patients with fractures and orthopaedic conditions. Excellent communication skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think you would like to be part of our team and are keen to take on a new challenge, then we would love to meet you. Informal visits welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact the dept on 01225 826380 and ask for Sisters Cathy Breeze or Andrea Morgan or Matron Laura Andrews, if you would like to arrange a visit, or for further information.&lt;/p&gt;
